{
  "texts": [
    "Targeted TPD initiatives that address these challenges could be key to overcoming barriers and advancing STEM education more broadly.",
    "Students' interest in STEM can be promoted through infrastructure improvements, innovation in teaching methods, and improved infrastructure.",
    "A review of the current literature reveals a noticeable research gap in STEM education in China, particularly in the teacher professional development (TPD) domain.",
    "STEM TPD programs have underexplored the following areas: The professional development and implementation of STEM teachers in China have been the subject of several recent studies, including those conducted by Stonier and Adarkwah (2023) and Ong et al. (2020).",
    "However, significant research gaps remain, particularly in the breadth and scope of TPD studies."
  ]
}